WEBVTT

00:02.809 --> 00:05.647
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:05.715 --> 00:08.386
[ Glasses clinking ]

00:08.454 --> 00:12.359
♪ Cryin' on the corner,
waitin' in the rain ♪

00:12.427 --> 00:16.367
♪ I swear
I'll never, ever wait again ♪

00:16.435 --> 00:18.603
♪ you gave me your word ♪

00:18.671 --> 00:24.011
♪ but words for you are lies ♪

00:24.078 --> 00:25.279
♪ darlin'... ♪

00:25.347 --> 00:28.951
Seriously? The president?

00:29.019 --> 00:30.286
At this level,

00:30.354 --> 00:33.155
there aren't that many people
he can trust.

00:33.223 --> 00:35.960
How do I know
you're not making all this up?

00:36.027 --> 00:37.696
♪ ...my heart ♪

00:37.764 --> 00:40.999
♪ I'm gonna swallow my tears ♪

00:41.067 --> 00:46.238
♪ I'm gonna turn
and leave you here ♪

00:46.306 --> 00:48.407
Oh, my God.

00:48.474 --> 00:52.175
♪ All of my life
I've been waitin' in the rain ♪

00:52.243 --> 00:53.843
So handsome.

00:53.911 --> 00:56.611
The things I'm telling you...

00:56.679 --> 00:58.947
You don't joke around about.

00:59.015 --> 01:02.117
It could be dangerous.

01:02.184 --> 01:05.053
Dangerous. Mm.

01:05.120 --> 01:08.121
♪ I'm gonna harden my heart ♪

01:08.189 --> 01:11.591
♪ I'm gonna swallow my tears ♪

01:11.658 --> 01:16.093
You know, most people...

01:16.161 --> 01:19.195
They get into their warm beds
at night.

01:19.263 --> 01:23.466
They have no idea
what really goes on out there.

01:23.534 --> 01:26.669
The sheer number of people

01:26.737 --> 01:30.439
working to destroy
our way of life.

01:30.506 --> 01:31.806
You... you know why

01:31.873 --> 01:35.975
I've dedicated my life
to stopping them?

01:36.042 --> 01:38.010
Why?

01:38.078 --> 01:40.679
Because...

01:40.746 --> 01:41.846
[ Groans ]

01:41.914 --> 01:43.148
Because...

01:43.215 --> 01:44.616
You ready for this?

01:44.684 --> 01:46.784
Oh.

01:46.852 --> 01:48.318
Oh.

01:48.386 --> 01:50.787
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:52.000 --> 01:58.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:00.061 --> 02:02.062
[ Keys jingling ]

02:09.698 --> 02:11.565
[ Engine turns over ]

02:20.939 --> 02:22.706
[ Vehicle departs ]

02:22.774 --> 02:26.477
[ Man speaking indistinctly
over p.A. System ]

02:34.419 --> 02:37.621
I don't know.
Think about something else.

02:37.688 --> 02:41.458
Take deep breaths.

02:41.525 --> 02:43.459
It's just...

02:43.527 --> 02:45.595
They used to tell stories
about this guy, you know?

02:45.662 --> 02:47.296
He killed a lot of people.

02:47.364 --> 02:49.765
You know how guys like him
kill people?

02:49.833 --> 02:52.434
They plan it for weeks, and
they always come up from behind.

02:52.502 --> 02:55.369
Fighting face-to-face,
that's a different story.

02:55.437 --> 02:57.738
Rob: I heard once
he got in a bar fight

02:57.805 --> 02:59.539
with the entire
Japanese olympic judo team.

02:59.607 --> 03:02.242
Took out four of 'em
before the rest of 'em ran.

03:02.309 --> 03:04.877
Which year?
Because '64 to '72 were pussies.

03:04.945 --> 03:06.279
They didn't even medal.

03:13.086 --> 03:15.654
Woman: I need to look out
your living room window

03:15.722 --> 03:17.455
for a few minutes.

03:20.259 --> 03:21.693
[ Chain lock disengages ]

03:25.864 --> 03:27.264
Philip: Time?

03:27.332 --> 03:28.465
Rob: Minus 22.

03:28.533 --> 03:30.234
No, what time is it?

03:30.301 --> 03:31.935
Um... It's 9:15.

03:32.003 --> 03:35.239
Mm. The capitals are in L.A.,
start soon.

03:35.307 --> 03:36.574
You follow the NHL?

03:36.641 --> 03:37.775
I like football.

03:37.843 --> 03:40.044
She's in.
Third floor, three east.

03:55.593 --> 03:57.561
He's at the corner.

04:49.679 --> 04:51.580
Philip: Immigration!
We just want to talk!

04:51.648 --> 04:53.583
[ Russian accent ] Help! Help!

04:53.651 --> 04:55.718
Help!

04:55.786 --> 04:58.454
Don't get too close!

04:58.522 --> 05:02.792
[ Fleetwood Mac's "Tusk" plays ]

05:02.860 --> 05:05.495
Philip: Watch the corner!

05:06.063 --> 05:08.164
Ugh!

05:21.078 --> 05:22.846
♪ Tusk ♪

05:34.894 --> 05:36.628
♪ tusk ♪

05:42.936 --> 05:44.938
[ Panting ]

05:45.005 --> 05:46.573
♪ Tusk ♪

05:46.641 --> 05:48.341
[ Music stops ]

06:07.900 --> 06:11.303
[ Bottle clatters ]

06:15.943 --> 06:18.411
[ Groans ]

06:18.478 --> 06:21.413
I know you're not
supposed to kill me.

06:21.481 --> 06:24.249
I don't think you understand
how unpopular you are.

06:24.317 --> 06:26.618
I could deliver you
in a hundred pieces.

06:26.686 --> 06:28.787
They'd give me
a separate medal for each one.

06:28.855 --> 06:30.823
[ "Tusk" resumes ]

06:33.126 --> 06:36.261
[ Tires screech ]

06:39.132 --> 06:42.734
He's not police! He's not police!
He's not police!

06:42.802 --> 06:44.736
- You have the right to remain silent!
- He's not really police!

06:44.804 --> 06:46.939
- Help! Call for help! Call for help!
- Anything you say and do will...

06:47.006 --> 06:49.108
can and will be used against you
in a court of law!

06:49.175 --> 06:50.543
Ohh!

07:01.188 --> 07:04.190
[ Engine revs, tires screech ]

07:05.626 --> 07:11.397
♪ Why don't you tell me
who's on the phone? ♪

07:11.464 --> 07:13.399
[ Tires screech ]

07:19.105 --> 07:21.139
Hey, hey! Keep your eyes open.

07:26.078 --> 07:30.147
All right. It's okay.
Deep breaths.

07:35.687 --> 07:37.288
Look at me. Rob? Rob?

07:42.161 --> 07:43.762
Keep your eyes on me.

07:44.898 --> 07:46.565
[ Tires screech ]

07:56.843 --> 07:58.844
[ Breathing heavily ]

08:04.051 --> 08:06.519
Heavy bleeding,
he's got 10, 15 minutes.

08:06.587 --> 08:08.054
Arlington Methodist,

08:08.122 --> 08:09.756
then 66 to the beltway
to the drop site?

08:09.823 --> 08:11.157
No, we blew our whole window
on the chase.

08:11.225 --> 08:12.425
We won't make it.

08:12.493 --> 08:13.960
So? Parkway to the beltway.

08:14.028 --> 08:15.295
He dies, and 50/50
we miss the hand off anyway.

08:15.363 --> 08:17.264
No, the mission comes first!

08:17.332 --> 08:19.133
I can help you.
I can make you rich.

08:19.201 --> 08:20.701
Shut up!

08:22.871 --> 08:24.938
[ Tires screech ]

08:38.386 --> 08:40.288
Philip: You go in a John Doe.

08:40.355 --> 08:41.923
If you live,
do not go back to Boston.

08:41.990 --> 08:43.491
[ Siren wailing ]
Assume they're on you.

08:43.558 --> 08:45.594
All right?
You got to walk from here.

08:45.661 --> 08:47.529
You were trained
to surmount any obstacle.

08:47.596 --> 08:49.330
Go!

08:49.398 --> 08:51.499
[ Breathing heavily ]

08:57.440 --> 08:59.808
[ Tires screech ]

08:59.876 --> 09:03.245
♪ Don't say that you love me ♪

09:05.648 --> 09:07.950
Back is clear.

09:08.018 --> 09:09.585
Time?

09:09.653 --> 09:10.886
Minus 7.

09:10.954 --> 09:12.188
There's another way, please.

09:12.255 --> 09:14.223
Listen to me.
We can all sit down...

09:14.290 --> 09:15.991
Shut up! [ Groans ]

09:18.027 --> 09:19.561
♪ Tusk ♪

09:21.397 --> 09:23.599
♪ just say that you want me ♪

09:31.341 --> 09:34.076
♪ don't tell me that you ♪

09:34.144 --> 09:36.545
♪ tusk ♪
♪ real savage like ♪

09:52.129 --> 09:54.230
Why is everyone so punctual
in this business?

09:55.674 --> 10:00.735
Sync and correction by GeirDM
www.addic7ed.com

10:02.822 --> 10:05.175
Counter Intelligence is the place
you wanna be right now Stan.

10:05.639 --> 10:07.907
I mean, what's it take
to rob a bank?

10:07.975 --> 10:09.375
Stick a couple fingers in your pocket
and say, "give me all your money"?

10:09.443 --> 10:10.610
In C.I, we're up against

10:10.678 --> 10:12.312
the most sophisticated enemy
in the world.

10:12.379 --> 10:13.813
I'll tell you one good thing
about bank robbers...

10:13.881 --> 10:15.381
they speak English.

10:15.449 --> 10:17.817
They got me in beginning Russian
four days a week.

10:17.884 --> 10:19.519
Ugh. You got an ear
for languages?

10:19.586 --> 10:21.521
Ah, you know, I had a very
attractive French teacher

10:21.589 --> 10:23.122
one year in high school.
I got a B-plus.

10:23.190 --> 10:24.957
Oh, coffee.

10:25.025 --> 10:26.358
Ah, just what I need.

10:26.426 --> 10:27.860
We getting started soon,
there, boss?

10:27.928 --> 10:29.629
Timoshev isn't here.
He's 20 minutes late.

10:29.697 --> 10:31.765
Maybe he had a little too much
vodka last night.

10:31.832 --> 10:34.601
I have been working with him
since he defected.

10:34.669 --> 10:36.970
He hasn't been 20 <i>seconds</i> late
for anything.

10:37.038 --> 10:38.405
Where's he coming in from?

10:38.472 --> 10:39.906
I don't know.

10:39.974 --> 10:41.641
He only deals with the director
and the A.G.

10:41.709 --> 10:43.276
I don't even know
where he stayed last night.

10:46.080 --> 10:47.815
Mormon.

10:47.882 --> 10:49.216
Since Reagan got elected,

10:49.284 --> 10:50.984
he starts these meetings
at 7:00 A.M.

10:51.052 --> 10:52.853
Reagan's not a mormon.

10:52.920 --> 10:54.988
Fundamentalist, whatever.
The goal is the same...

10:55.056 --> 10:57.324
to wear down the enemy by
waking up earlier than they do.

10:57.391 --> 11:00.927
Who's Timoshev?

11:00.995 --> 11:02.262
He's this ex-KGB colonel.

11:02.330 --> 11:03.630
Blew the whistle

11:03.698 --> 11:05.533
on these Directorate "S"
undercover agents

11:05.600 --> 11:07.435
supposedly hiding
all over the U.S.

11:07.503 --> 11:08.737
Super-secret identities...

11:08.804 --> 11:10.472
no one has any idea
who they are.

11:10.540 --> 11:12.040
What, you don't buy it?

11:12.108 --> 11:13.475
There's not a single piece
of evidence.

11:13.543 --> 11:15.812
Look. You get these guys
like Timoshev, right?

11:15.879 --> 11:17.313
They come over.

11:17.381 --> 11:18.882
They get these huge
resettlement packages.

11:18.949 --> 11:20.817
We're talking
millions of dollars.

11:20.884 --> 11:22.685
So, they say things to us
to justify it.

11:22.753 --> 11:24.554
They make up stories
to make us happy.

11:24.622 --> 11:26.522
Super-secret spies
living next door.

11:26.590 --> 11:28.124
They look like us, they speak
better English than we do.

11:28.192 --> 11:30.460
According to Timoshev,

11:30.528 --> 11:32.663
they're not allowed to say a single
word in Russian once they get here.

11:32.730 --> 11:35.499
I mean, come on. Someone's been
reading too many spy novels.

11:35.567 --> 11:37.935
We're talking figment
of the imagination.

11:39.271 --> 11:41.673
You understand
you make any noise,

11:41.740 --> 11:43.341
I will kill you immediately.

11:44.076 --> 11:46.144
[ Gasps, coughs ]

11:47.947 --> 11:50.982
FBI paid me $3 million
when I came over

11:51.050 --> 11:53.518
and more since as a consultant.

11:53.586 --> 11:55.387
You can get twice that!

11:55.454 --> 12:00.192
$3 million
as the most valued of defectors,

12:01.995 --> 12:06.732
a Directorate "S" officer.

12:06.800 --> 12:11.103
Another $3 million
for returning me.

12:11.171 --> 12:14.507
Just go to the FBI
and tell them...

12:14.574 --> 12:15.708
[ gagging ]

12:22.883 --> 12:24.650
Car won't start!

12:24.717 --> 12:27.486
We're gonna have to take the bus
to the Metro.

12:27.554 --> 12:29.154
- Oh, dad.
- Yeah?

12:29.222 --> 12:31.590
Maruk got two goals and an
assist last night versus L.A.

12:31.658 --> 12:32.925
[ Water running ] Did they win?

12:32.993 --> 12:34.193
Uh, no. It was a tie.

12:34.261 --> 12:35.795
I'm not going in today,

12:35.863 --> 12:37.630
so you're gonna have to handle
Portland rotary

12:37.698 --> 12:39.599
and call Swissair.

12:39.667 --> 12:42.770
Do you know how much
they paid that asshole?

12:42.837 --> 12:44.204
$3 million.

12:44.272 --> 12:45.839
Henry was looking
for his skateboard.

12:45.907 --> 12:47.141
It's not in the garage, is it?

12:47.209 --> 12:48.276
No.

12:48.343 --> 12:50.177
[ Water shuts off ]

12:51.713 --> 12:53.881
- Let's go, Henry.
- Huh?

12:56.384 --> 12:58.318
- Bye.
- Bye.

12:58.385 --> 12:59.753
Bye, guys.

12:59.820 --> 13:02.089
What, no coffee for you?

13:02.156 --> 13:03.557
Uh, no, thanks.

13:03.624 --> 13:05.492
[ Door opens ]

13:05.559 --> 13:06.760
[ Door closes ]

13:06.827 --> 13:08.462
We have to get rid of him
tonight.

13:08.529 --> 13:10.630
I just coded the message,
I'll drop it on the way to work.

13:10.698 --> 13:13.033
You don't have to stay here.
He's secure in there.

13:13.101 --> 13:14.835
There were witnesses.
If they figure it out,

13:14.903 --> 13:17.204
I mean, they could be looking
for him in a couple of hours.

13:17.272 --> 13:19.707
- I'm gonna stay. - Yeah, told
you... we should have built

13:19.775 --> 13:22.043
that secret underground chamber
in the basement.

13:22.111 --> 13:23.478
You mean the wine cellar

13:23.546 --> 13:25.480
you wanted to put in
under the laundry room?

13:25.547 --> 13:27.181
I did say
it could have other uses.

13:27.249 --> 13:30.985
Anyway, $3 million?

13:31.053 --> 13:34.622
He can buy himself
a diamond-plated coffin.

13:36.992 --> 13:39.461
[ Children playing in distance ]

13:54.211 --> 13:55.578
[ Baby cooing ]

13:55.645 --> 13:59.148
[ Police radio chatter ]

13:59.216 --> 14:02.718
1-7. Show me on this location.
Show me canvassing.

14:02.786 --> 14:05.654
Dispatcher: Multiple callers,
unknown direction of flight.

14:05.722 --> 14:07.523
What do you got?

14:07.590 --> 14:09.558
I got a female witness.

14:09.625 --> 14:11.459
She saw a guy
knock the victim down,

14:11.527 --> 14:13.195
grab the purse,
and run this way.

14:13.262 --> 14:16.732
Give me that, uh... description
one more time, please.

14:16.800 --> 14:18.434
We didn't get
a full description.

14:18.501 --> 14:21.203
Male Caucasian, black hair,
unknown complexion, unknown age.

14:21.271 --> 14:22.538
All right,
if you do have a victim,

14:22.605 --> 14:23.606
have them respond
to this location...

14:23.673 --> 14:26.709
north end of Dupont Circle.

14:26.777 --> 14:28.210
All right, did you
notify Parks?

14:28.278 --> 14:29.745
[ Police radio chatter ]

14:29.813 --> 14:33.482
[ Indistinct conversation ]

15:11.657 --> 15:14.326
[ Rhythmic punching ]

15:21.734 --> 15:23.268
[ Grunting ]
[ Russian accent ] Again.

15:30.676 --> 15:32.210
[ Chuckles ]

15:32.278 --> 15:34.379
Harder. Focus.

15:39.218 --> 15:40.619
Yeah.

15:40.686 --> 15:42.821
Okay. Again.

15:42.889 --> 15:44.956
So, what we have?

15:45.024 --> 15:46.792
Captain...

15:46.859 --> 15:48.594
I did not know you are back.

15:48.661 --> 15:50.796
You two are working late.

15:50.864 --> 15:52.331
She has great promise.

15:52.399 --> 15:54.366
We are putting in extra work.

16:07.981 --> 16:09.582
Leave us.

16:09.650 --> 16:11.751
I will teach her how we do it
in the field.

16:15.856 --> 16:17.657
Go.

16:22.229 --> 16:23.896
Now, my dear...

16:27.601 --> 16:29.268
again.

16:39.446 --> 16:41.948
[ Russian accent ]
I am sorry, Captain.

16:42.015 --> 16:43.315
<i>I'm</i> sorry.

16:43.383 --> 16:44.650
Use the contraction.

16:44.718 --> 16:47.453
I'm sorry.

16:47.520 --> 16:50.122
Now... faster.

16:52.559 --> 16:53.826
Ugh!

16:53.893 --> 16:55.527
Watch!

16:55.595 --> 16:59.700
Don't overcommit.

17:06.740 --> 17:08.540
[ Groans ]

17:14.381 --> 17:15.815
[ Grunting ]

17:15.883 --> 17:17.050
Nyet!

17:21.888 --> 17:23.789
[ Fabric ripping ]

17:26.425 --> 17:28.294
[ Belt buckle clinking ]

17:32.566 --> 17:35.501
[ Screams ]

17:35.569 --> 17:37.803
[ Grunting ]

17:50.182 --> 17:53.251
[ Normal voice ]
Remember me, Captain?

18:01.823 --> 18:02.888
How's the game?

18:03.224 --> 18:04.791
Uh, Jughead is
in serious trouble.

18:04.859 --> 18:08.128
Okay, well, do some reading
and some stirring for me, okay?

18:08.196 --> 18:10.430
- Paige, what are you working on?
- Social studies...

18:10.498 --> 18:13.901
a paper on how the Russians
cheat on arms control.

18:13.968 --> 18:17.371
Hmm.
That's, uh, Henrickson, right?

18:17.439 --> 18:19.006
- Yep.
- Yeah.

18:19.074 --> 18:21.375
I don't know how
you can look at him all day

18:21.443 --> 18:22.910
with that... that harelip.

18:22.978 --> 18:25.479
Mom, that's his handicap.

18:28.216 --> 18:30.550
So, what's the trouble
with these guys?

18:30.618 --> 18:33.520
Well, Betty and Veronica
were hosting a charity drive,

18:33.587 --> 18:34.854
- and...
- Yeah?

18:34.922 --> 18:36.656
- So Jughead...
Philip: - I'm home!

18:36.723 --> 18:38.091
- Oh, dad!
- Yeah?

18:38.158 --> 18:40.460
We launched
our rocket today in science.

18:40.527 --> 18:42.862
- Wow! Was it manned or unmanned?
- Unmanned.

18:42.930 --> 18:45.031
But tomorrow, we're gonna give
Commander Stafford a plaque

18:45.098 --> 18:46.265
to commemorate the mission.

18:46.333 --> 18:48.668
Well, I'm sure
he'll be very honored.

18:48.736 --> 18:50.003
[ Quietly ]
Go look out the window.

18:53.508 --> 18:55.876
[ Exhaust fan running ]

18:55.944 --> 18:58.112
I made the drop in the park.
No response.

18:58.180 --> 19:00.315
Maybe he can move in with us
permanently.

19:00.383 --> 19:02.450
I can fix up
the spare bedroom for him.

19:02.518 --> 19:05.421
I have a meeting later.
We'll know more then.

19:06.657 --> 19:08.291
Henry: Holy shit!

19:08.358 --> 19:09.892
That's the coolest car ever!

19:09.960 --> 19:11.193
Henry! Language!

19:11.261 --> 19:13.162
Don't fall in love with it.

19:13.230 --> 19:15.765
It's only a rental
until the Oldsmobile gets fixed.

19:15.832 --> 19:17.701
I said that word once, and
you guys grounded me for a week.

19:19.236 --> 19:21.304
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:23.040 --> 19:25.075
Whenever you're ready.

19:25.143 --> 19:26.709
Here we go.

19:26.777 --> 19:28.144
Dad's gonna start this up
right here, right now.

19:28.212 --> 19:31.848
Ice-cream Olympics.
Take your time.

19:31.916 --> 19:34.050
- Eyes on the cone.
- Be the cone.

19:34.118 --> 19:36.153
Eyes... eyes on the cone.
Don't feint too early.

19:36.220 --> 19:39.223
Don't feint too early.
[ Chuckles ]

19:39.291 --> 19:42.559
Know your distance.
Know your distance.

19:44.762 --> 19:46.530
Oh, no!

19:46.597 --> 19:47.797
[ Laughs ]

19:47.865 --> 19:51.334
All right, Henry, you're up.

19:51.402 --> 19:52.836
War... paint.

19:52.904 --> 19:54.271
Here we go.

19:54.339 --> 19:56.540
War paint.
Let me see your war face.

19:56.608 --> 19:58.542
Spike it.

19:58.610 --> 20:00.844
Eyes on the cone.

20:01.746 --> 20:03.213
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

20:03.281 --> 20:04.614
Ease up. Remember the training.

20:04.682 --> 20:06.216
Ohh!

20:06.284 --> 20:08.619
The big nose cone!

20:08.686 --> 20:10.087
- Mom, you're up.
- No, thanks.

20:10.155 --> 20:12.322
Come on. Just a... just a...

20:12.390 --> 20:13.557
I don't want... no, thanks.

20:13.625 --> 20:14.958
Little one?
Come on. Let's see. Ohh!

20:15.026 --> 20:16.493
[ Snickers ]

20:18.996 --> 20:21.098
- Sorry.
- Stop.

20:21.166 --> 20:23.367
Maybe we can have a Checkers
round-robin when we get hone?

20:23.435 --> 20:25.569
Um, I'm just dropping
you guys off.

20:25.637 --> 20:27.638
I got to...
got to meet a client.

20:27.706 --> 20:29.907
Why are you meeting
a client so late?

20:29.975 --> 20:32.142
He's coming in on a late flight
and wants to grab a drink.

20:32.210 --> 20:34.511
You know, that's what business
is all about, honey.

20:34.579 --> 20:36.279
Anyone can make
travel arrangements,

20:36.347 --> 20:38.915
but you keep
the executives happy,

20:38.983 --> 20:40.617
you keep the accounts.

21:08.345 --> 21:11.247
[ Doorbell rings ]

21:15.252 --> 21:17.454
How have you been, Martha?

21:17.521 --> 21:19.790
Fine, Clark.
Would you like to come in?

21:23.561 --> 21:25.229
So, referencing
our meeting this evening...

21:25.297 --> 21:27.932
obviously, you understand
it's been classified Top Secret

21:27.999 --> 21:29.500
by the the Internal
Affairs Division

21:29.567 --> 21:31.101
of the Committee to oversee

21:31.169 --> 21:34.071
United States'
counterintelligence agencies.

21:34.139 --> 21:35.472
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth,

21:35.540 --> 21:37.742
- et cetera, et cetera?
- I do.

21:37.809 --> 21:41.912
Great. So, big day
at FBI Counterintelligence?

21:41.980 --> 21:43.280
Yes, it was.

21:43.348 --> 21:44.648
Obviously, we know most of it,

21:44.716 --> 21:46.484
but I just want to hear
the details from you,

21:46.551 --> 21:48.919
because a crisis
can provide an opportunity

21:48.987 --> 21:50.421
to uncover the leaks

21:50.489 --> 21:52.823
that we have been looking for
in your office.

21:52.891 --> 21:55.793
So just tell me what you saw.

21:57.196 --> 21:58.462
Thank you.

21:58.530 --> 22:00.131
Well...

22:00.198 --> 22:03.234
I-I know
that a man was kidnapped.

22:03.301 --> 22:06.637
He was supposed to speak
at a conference this morning,

22:06.705 --> 22:07.905
but he didn't show.

22:07.973 --> 22:09.373
Mm-hmm.

22:09.441 --> 22:10.708
And did there appear to be
a centralized response

22:10.776 --> 22:12.042
to the kidnapping?

22:12.110 --> 22:14.778
They were
in the secure vault all day.

22:14.846 --> 22:16.480
Did you get a look inside
this time?

22:16.547 --> 22:18.114
[ Chuckles ]

22:18.182 --> 22:21.251
They don't let me in there.
And you know that.

22:21.319 --> 22:22.552
I know. I'm sorry.

22:22.620 --> 22:25.890
Please go on.

22:25.957 --> 22:28.593
Um...

22:28.660 --> 22:32.063
well, the man that
they kidnapped was Russian.

22:32.131 --> 22:35.734
He was someone very important
in the KGB, I think.

22:35.802 --> 22:37.903
- Right.
- By early afternoon,

22:37.971 --> 22:41.707
they had tied it to a police
report in northeast D.C.

22:41.775 --> 22:44.811
about a man who was kidnapped
last night.

22:44.878 --> 22:46.746
And they have
a vehicle description,

22:46.814 --> 22:49.048
'77 Oldsmobile, gold,

22:49.116 --> 22:53.086
with D.C. plates
and bumper stickers.

22:53.154 --> 22:55.355
And descriptions
of the kidnappers?

22:55.423 --> 22:57.023
Two men and a woman.

22:57.091 --> 23:00.827
One of the men...
average height with dark hair.

23:00.895 --> 23:05.798
And what specific actions
did Agent Bartholomew order?

23:05.866 --> 23:09.769
Extra agents were sent
to surveil the Soviet embassy,

23:09.836 --> 23:13.739
agents went out to all the ports
and train stations.

23:13.807 --> 23:15.775
They thought the Russians

23:15.842 --> 23:17.777
would take the man
out of the country.

23:17.844 --> 23:20.413
How would you best describe
Agent Bartholomew's mood?

23:20.481 --> 23:21.914
Angry?

23:21.982 --> 23:24.351
Um...

23:24.418 --> 23:26.453
but I-I don't want to get him
in trouble.

23:26.521 --> 23:28.388
No, no, no, no. Not at all.

23:28.456 --> 23:31.625
[ Stammers, sighs ]

23:31.693 --> 23:33.293
Our counterintelligence units,

23:33.360 --> 23:36.830
they safeguard the security
of our nation, Martha.

23:36.897 --> 23:40.233
So, we have to safeguard
<i>their</i> security.

24:15.337 --> 24:17.438
[ Button clicks ]

24:17.506 --> 24:20.508
[ <i>Man moaning</i> ]

24:22.143 --> 24:23.978
Elizabeth:
<i>Tell me what you want next.</i>

24:24.046 --> 24:26.014
Man: <i>Oh. I don't know.</i>

24:26.081 --> 24:27.882
<i>How about... this?</i>

24:27.950 --> 24:30.752
Oh, I... oh, I don't know.
<i>I don't... oh!</i>

24:30.819 --> 24:33.221
<i>Oh, yes!</i>

24:33.322 --> 24:35.190
You mean to tell me

24:35.258 --> 24:37.692
<i>a girl never put her finger</i>
<i>up your ass before?</i>

24:37.760 --> 24:40.628
[ <i>Moaning</i> ]

24:40.696 --> 24:42.630
<i>That's right.</i>

24:42.698 --> 24:44.532
<i>Yeah, yeah. Now you got it.</i>

24:44.599 --> 24:45.833
<i>Mm-hmm.</i>

24:45.900 --> 24:47.534
[ Tape fast-forwards ]

24:47.602 --> 24:49.803
[ Button clicks ] <i>Oh, God.</i>

24:49.871 --> 24:53.674
[ Moaning ]
<i>Yeah. Yeah. Yeah. Oh!</i>

24:53.741 --> 24:55.542
[ Tape fast-forwards ]

24:55.610 --> 24:57.345
<i>There's something...</i>

24:57.412 --> 25:01.415
<i>I mean, if I... if I were</i>
<i>gonna see you again...</i>

25:01.483 --> 25:04.885
<i>I'd want you to be a little...</i>

25:04.953 --> 25:07.155
<i>What?</i>

25:07.222 --> 25:10.257
<i>I don't want to hurt</i>
<i>your feelings.</i>

25:10.325 --> 25:11.558
<i>Tell me.</i>

25:11.626 --> 25:15.095
<i>But just maybe...</i>

25:15.163 --> 25:17.197
<i>Stronger, maybe?</i>

25:21.769 --> 25:25.671
<i>Do you know what the KGB is?</i>

25:25.739 --> 25:28.074
<i>Um... I've heard of them.</i>

25:28.141 --> 25:29.876
<i>Well...</i>

25:29.943 --> 25:35.781
<i>Well, this weekend,</i>
<i>I am giving $100,000 cash</i>

25:35.849 --> 25:39.419
<i>to a KGB defector</i>
<i>who's coming to town to...</i>

25:39.486 --> 25:40.686
[ tape stops ]

25:48.411 --> 25:50.439
The Reagan administration
revealed today

25:50.564 --> 25:52.198
<i>that after a month-long review,</i>

25:52.266 --> 25:53.933
<i>it will honor the agreement</i>
<i>with Iran</i>

25:54.001 --> 25:56.269
<i>that led to the release</i>
<i>of the 52 American hostages.</i>

25:56.336 --> 25:59.906
So...

25:59.974 --> 26:03.076
FBI have the car description
with the D.C. plates.

26:03.144 --> 26:04.778
They haven't connected it

26:04.845 --> 26:07.981
to a stabbing victim
at Arlington Methodist yet,

26:08.049 --> 26:10.350
but I don't think
it will be long.

26:10.418 --> 26:12.252
They're all over our guys
at the embassy,

26:12.320 --> 26:13.888
who must have made
the surveillance,

26:13.956 --> 26:15.857
which is why they can't get out

26:15.924 --> 26:17.925
to pick up my message
or respond.

26:17.993 --> 26:19.226
So, I think we have to assume,

26:19.294 --> 26:20.828
with the feds
all over them like that,

26:20.896 --> 26:24.699
they're on full operational
stand-down.

26:24.766 --> 26:27.601
We should just
take care of him ourselves.

26:27.669 --> 26:29.103
What's the rush?

26:29.171 --> 26:31.906
On an operational stand-down,

26:31.974 --> 26:35.243
we're authorized to make
our own decisions.

26:35.311 --> 26:38.512
Yes, but why do you want
to kill him so badly?

26:38.580 --> 26:40.548
I want him out of my house!

26:40.616 --> 26:42.417
He's putting us all in danger,

26:42.485 --> 26:44.352
and they're just gonna kill him
back in Moscow anyway.

26:44.420 --> 26:46.954
I think we should at least try
and finish the mission

26:47.022 --> 26:48.090
the way it was assigned.

26:48.157 --> 26:49.858
Oh, <i>now</i> you want to complete the
mission the way it was assigned?

26:50.126 --> 26:51.660
I mean, you should have
thought of that before, Philip.

26:51.727 --> 26:52.728
He shouldn't even be here.

26:52.795 --> 26:54.529
Well, if you're
that worried about him,

26:54.597 --> 26:56.365
maybe we could just defect
ourselves.

26:56.433 --> 26:59.268
At least we'd be millionaires.

26:59.335 --> 27:02.537
Hmm? We wouldn't have to worry
about going to jail

27:02.605 --> 27:04.339
and leaving the kids all alone.

27:04.407 --> 27:06.541
A lot of our problems
would just go away.

27:06.609 --> 27:08.677
Pkew!

27:08.745 --> 27:11.312
That's very funny.

27:15.184 --> 27:18.387
Let's see
what we hear tomorrow.

27:18.454 --> 27:21.323
[ TV clicks off ]

27:30.499 --> 27:32.399
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:35.437 --> 27:37.571
You sure
you don't want to come?

27:37.639 --> 27:39.740
Haven't even seen
the new mall yet.

27:39.807 --> 27:42.375
It's a mall.

27:42.443 --> 27:44.144
Henry: See you, ma.

27:44.212 --> 27:47.514
Yeah, I know, but this one has
fountains and skylights.

27:47.582 --> 27:49.183
Bye, mom.

27:53.289 --> 27:55.056
[ Car door closes ]

27:55.124 --> 27:57.092
When we went to dinner
last week,

27:57.159 --> 28:00.128
wasn't she wearing a sweater
with a bunny rabbit on it?

28:00.195 --> 28:01.763
Oh, my God.

28:04.566 --> 28:07.334
♪ Playing with
the Queen of hearts ♪

28:07.402 --> 28:09.036
♪ knowin' it
ain't really smart ♪

28:09.104 --> 28:10.671
Really?

28:10.739 --> 28:12.072
Just call your parents.

28:12.140 --> 28:13.607
Tell them you're sleeping
at Lisa's house.

28:13.675 --> 28:16.109
Do you think I'm gonna get
in trouble?

28:16.177 --> 28:18.378
♪ Laying out another lie ♪

28:18.445 --> 28:21.181
♪ thinkin' 'bout
a life of crime ♪

28:21.248 --> 28:23.716
♪ 'cause that's
what I'll have to do ♪

28:23.784 --> 28:26.252
Thanks.
♪ to keep me away from you ♪

28:28.221 --> 28:31.290
♪ honey ♪

28:31.358 --> 28:34.026
♪ you know it makes you mad ♪

28:34.094 --> 28:35.995
♪ why is everybody tellin'
everybody ♪

28:36.063 --> 28:37.897
♪ what you have done? ♪

28:39.767 --> 28:41.701
♪ baby ♪

28:41.769 --> 28:45.405
♪ I know it makes you sad ♪

28:45.472 --> 28:47.073
♪ but when they're handin' out
the heartaches ♪

28:47.141 --> 28:50.877
♪ you know
you got to have you some ♪

28:50.945 --> 28:53.447
♪ playin' with
the Queen of hearts ♪

28:53.515 --> 28:56.150
♪ knowin'
it ain't really smart ♪

28:56.218 --> 28:57.952
♪ the joker ain't the only... ♪

29:00.556 --> 29:01.923
Whoa.

29:01.990 --> 29:03.891
I like that.

29:05.761 --> 29:08.128
You look nice, darlin'.

29:08.196 --> 29:10.064
You want to come with me and Dee
to shop for makeup

29:10.131 --> 29:11.799
after you pay for those?

29:18.573 --> 29:21.175
Errol, she's 13.

29:21.243 --> 29:22.810
13?

29:22.878 --> 29:24.712
I don't know, daddy.

29:24.780 --> 29:26.781
She sure looks ready to me.

29:29.685 --> 29:31.853
[ Chuckles softly ]

29:36.259 --> 29:38.861
[ Sighs ]

29:40.230 --> 29:42.898
So long, honey.

29:42.966 --> 29:44.467
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

29:44.534 --> 29:46.302
Come on.

29:49.839 --> 29:52.641
You're, uh, getting older,
so...

29:52.709 --> 29:54.843
I know, I know.

29:54.911 --> 29:57.612
It's... it's no use
fighting guys like that.

29:57.680 --> 30:00.682
Oh, God,
I wouldn't want you to.

30:00.750 --> 30:02.717
[ Timer dings ]

30:39.989 --> 30:41.689
[ Tires screech ]

30:46.728 --> 30:49.296
You don't have to be a cowboy
to wear cowboy boots.

30:49.364 --> 30:50.931
Jaden says you do.

30:50.999 --> 30:52.600
Paige: No one wears
cowboy boots anymore, dad.

30:52.668 --> 30:56.770
You know, dad,
she does have a point there.

30:59.274 --> 31:00.841
I met the new neighbors.

31:00.908 --> 31:03.243
We're gonna over later
to say hello.

31:09.383 --> 31:12.319
What, do you think
I killed him?

31:12.386 --> 31:14.620
Just checking.

31:20.727 --> 31:22.061
Stop.

31:25.633 --> 31:27.601
Stop.

31:32.975 --> 31:35.844
You're my wife.

31:35.911 --> 31:37.412
Is that right?

31:47.090 --> 31:50.126
[ Doorbell rings ]

31:50.193 --> 31:51.794
Oh, hi. You came!

31:51.861 --> 31:53.562
Just for a second,
to, uh, bring over brownies

31:53.630 --> 31:55.030
and welcome you
to the neighborhood.

31:55.098 --> 31:57.399
Well, come in. Come in.

31:57.467 --> 31:58.734
Can I offer you guys
a drink or...?

31:58.801 --> 31:59.968
Philip: No, no, no, no, no.
Elizabeth: No.

32:00.036 --> 32:01.837
This place is a mess.

32:01.905 --> 32:03.205
Please, please,
don't do anything.

32:03.273 --> 32:05.074
We just wanted to bring over
the brownies.

32:05.141 --> 32:06.142
I'm so sorry.

32:06.209 --> 32:08.044
We can come over and help.

32:08.111 --> 32:10.780
Actually, Henry can come over
all day tomorrow if you want.

32:10.848 --> 32:13.317
Oh thank you. Um, this is my son Matthew.
Philip: Hi.

32:13.385 --> 32:15.386
Do you know
where your father is?

32:15.453 --> 32:16.687
Matthew: Uh, he's upstairs.

32:16.755 --> 32:18.322
What, do we have visitors
already?

32:18.390 --> 32:19.490
Uh, yeah. This is Stan.

32:19.558 --> 32:21.392
Hey. Phil Jennings.

32:21.460 --> 32:22.927
How you doing? Stan Beeman.

32:22.995 --> 32:24.929
Uh, my wife, Elizabeth,
Paige, Henry.

32:24.997 --> 32:26.364
- Hi.
- Hi.

32:26.432 --> 32:27.666
Hey, Henry.

32:27.733 --> 32:29.400
[ Clears throat ] Hello.

32:29.468 --> 32:32.470
- Ooh, are those brownies?
- Homemade.

32:32.538 --> 32:34.473
- May I?
- Mm.

32:34.540 --> 32:36.208
Your mom's a good cook?

32:36.275 --> 32:37.476
Yes.

32:37.543 --> 32:39.812
Okay.

32:39.880 --> 32:42.615
- I should've taken them.
Thank you. - Mmm.

32:42.683 --> 32:44.216
- Oh, that's a good brownie, hon.
- Yeah.

32:44.284 --> 32:46.052
So, this is a pretty good
neighborhood we moved into, huh?

32:46.119 --> 32:47.787
Philip:
Wouldn't live anywhere else.

32:47.854 --> 32:50.189
You know? Safe, clean.
Commute to D.C.'s not too bad.

32:50.257 --> 32:52.024
Do you work in the city?

32:52.092 --> 32:53.293
I do.

32:53.360 --> 32:54.394
What do...
what do you do, Stan?

32:54.461 --> 32:56.462
I'm an FBI agent.

32:56.530 --> 33:02.235
FBI? Wow! What... what, do you
catch bank robbers and stuff?

33:02.303 --> 33:04.571
Actually, I work
in Counterintelligence now.

33:04.639 --> 33:07.007
Counterintel... that's...
that's against spies, right?

33:07.075 --> 33:08.108
Exactly.

33:08.176 --> 33:09.977
Oh. I'll have to make sure

33:10.045 --> 33:12.179
I don't do any spying
around here.

33:12.247 --> 33:14.515
Oh, you better not,
especially for those Russians.

33:14.583 --> 33:16.350
Oh, yeah. They're the...
they're the worst, right?

33:16.417 --> 33:18.452
Oh, they certainly are, Philip.

33:18.519 --> 33:21.121
They certainly are.

33:26.899 --> 33:28.358
It's probably a coincidence,

33:28.650 --> 33:31.152
FBI agents
have to live somewhere.

33:31.219 --> 33:33.554
Or they're onto us.

33:33.622 --> 33:35.356
And this is what?

33:35.423 --> 33:36.991
The end game.

33:37.058 --> 33:39.226
They're... they're trying to
make us do something stupid.

33:39.293 --> 33:41.628
Either way, we get rid
of Timoshev tonight.

33:41.696 --> 33:43.697
I almost did it myself
this morning,

33:43.764 --> 33:45.431
but I thought you'd be pissed.

33:45.499 --> 33:46.933
If they are watching us,

33:47.000 --> 33:49.702
the last thing
you want to do is kill Timoshev.

33:49.770 --> 33:52.538
That's life in prison.
That's no deals, nothing.

33:52.606 --> 33:54.240
We take those risks every day,
Philip.

33:54.308 --> 33:55.341
That's what we do.

33:57.111 --> 33:59.879
May...
maybe there's another way.

34:01.883 --> 34:06.220
Look, maybe this is
an... opportunity.

34:06.288 --> 34:09.757
Maybe this is the perfect time
for us just to think about...

34:09.824 --> 34:12.060
living the life
we've been living

34:12.128 --> 34:13.929
but just really living it.

34:13.996 --> 34:16.699
Just... being us.

34:16.766 --> 34:19.569
What are you talking about?

34:19.637 --> 34:21.469
I'm saying we might be blown.

34:21.538 --> 34:23.472
And I'm saying
if they are watching us,

34:23.540 --> 34:25.007
we can't kill Timoshev.

34:25.074 --> 34:28.277
I'm also saying we are
Philip and Elizabeth Jennings.

34:28.344 --> 34:30.879
We have been
for a very long time.

34:30.947 --> 34:33.915
So why don't we get ahead
of this

34:33.983 --> 34:36.551
and why don't we make
the first move

34:36.619 --> 34:39.420
and offer ourselves to them?

34:39.487 --> 34:40.922
We could get a lot of money...

34:40.989 --> 34:43.891
$3 million for Timoshev,
$3 million for us.

34:43.960 --> 34:47.262
We just get relocated,
take the good life,

34:47.329 --> 34:49.397
and be happy.

34:52.202 --> 34:55.971
Are you joking?

34:56.039 --> 34:57.807
Is this a joke?

34:57.875 --> 35:00.109
No.

35:00.177 --> 35:01.344
You want to betray our country?

35:01.412 --> 35:02.712
Well, after
everything we've done,

35:02.780 --> 35:04.080
I don't think
it's such a betrayal.

35:04.148 --> 35:05.615
Defecting to America?

35:05.683 --> 35:09.320
America's not so bad.
We've been here a long time.

35:09.388 --> 35:12.323
What's... what's so bad
about it, you know?

35:12.391 --> 35:14.992
The electricity works all the time.
Food's pretty great.

35:15.060 --> 35:16.627
- The closet space...
- Is that what you care about?

35:16.695 --> 35:18.562
- No, I care about everything.
- Not the Motherland!

35:18.630 --> 35:20.931
I do, but our family
comes first.

35:20.999 --> 35:23.267
So, Paige and Henry, uh...

35:23.335 --> 35:25.836
- What exactly is your plan? - We'd have
a great life because we would have money.

35:25.904 --> 35:27.839
What would you tell them,
Philip?

35:27.906 --> 35:29.106
The truth.

35:31.877 --> 35:33.711
You swore.

35:33.779 --> 35:36.547
We swore
we would never tell them!

35:36.615 --> 35:38.983
To let them grow up
and live their own lives.

35:39.051 --> 35:40.685
They're not to be
a part of this.

35:40.753 --> 35:42.186
They're not
to be a part of this.

35:42.254 --> 35:44.121
They will be American,
and you can't stand that.

35:44.189 --> 35:45.523
I see it every day.

35:45.591 --> 35:46.958
I'm not finished with them yet.

35:47.025 --> 35:48.759
They don't have to be
regular Americans.

35:48.827 --> 35:51.195
- They can be socialists.
- They're not gonna be socialists.

35:51.263 --> 35:53.031
- They can be trade-union activists.
- This place doesn't turn out socialists.

35:53.098 --> 35:54.665
To know that it was all a lie?

35:54.733 --> 35:56.800
They would never speak to us
again, Philip.

35:56.868 --> 35:58.602
And what are we even
talking about?

35:58.670 --> 36:00.070
There would be no future
for any of us.

36:00.138 --> 36:02.806
- They would kill us all!
- They'd never find us.

36:02.874 --> 36:04.708
- They would never find us.
- Have you looked in our trunk?!

36:04.775 --> 36:07.010
He was a fool.

36:07.077 --> 36:09.178
He came back to give speeches.

36:09.246 --> 36:11.380
Left clues
about where he was staying.

36:11.448 --> 36:13.949
We'd... we'd be more careful.

36:21.791 --> 36:23.693
[ Sighs ]

37:01.166 --> 37:03.200
